OL,6,FAlthough butterflies were hit by a wet
OL,7,Fspring and cool summer, the charity
OL,8,Fsaid that these natural variations
OL,9,Fcome on top of long-term serious
OL,10,Fdeclines, driven by habitat loss and
OL,11,Fextreme weather from climate change.
OL,13,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,14,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,15,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,16,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,18,FDr Richard Fox, head of science at
OL,19,FButterfly Conservation, said pesticide
OL,20,Fpollution was also a key factor.
